description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Psychiatric Liaison Team based at Sunderland Royal Hospital. This as a well established PLAN accredited team, which is unique in its ageless approach.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will need to be flexible in their approach, to respond to the needs of the service and demands of a busy acute hospital. The role consists of providing assessment and brief interventions to all age ranges, who are presenting with a range of mental health needs to Sunderland Royal Hospital including self harm and delirium.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is a 24 hour service, across 7 days, which provides a responsive interface between both NHS and non NHS services including drug and alcohol services and other professions. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for applications from candidates who have a keen interest in the interplay between physical and mental health needs, within an acute hospital. The ideal candidate will be proactive and dynamic with experience of managing high levels of fluid complex risk, and brief psychological interventions. They will be able to demonstrate effective assessment skills and the ability to signpost onto relevant services in a timely manner. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an exciting time for Psychiatric Liaison Services as we continue to expand and adapt to the changing demands in line with local and national drivers&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;br /&gt;Samantha Diston (Team Manager)&lt;br /&gt;Tel : 0191 541 0145&lt;br /&gt;Mob : 07929 059768&lt;br /&gt;Email : samantha.diston@cntw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Hodgson (Community Clinical Manager) &lt;br /&gt;Mob: 07973982852&lt;br /&gt;Email: emmageorgina.hodgson@cntw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
